{"questionId":"35033819","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows a park bounded by a fence in the shape of a quadrilateral <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>ABCD</mtext></math>. A straight path crosses through the park from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>85</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>AD</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>85</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>BC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>C</mtext><mover><mtext>B</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>D</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>B</mtext><mover><mtext>C</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>D</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>120</mn><mo>°</mo></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/cf5c1f3d8dceb95dbd0d989858e69331e40cc87e.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The size of angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext><mover><mtext>A</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>D</mtext></math> rounds to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>77</mn><mo>°</mo></math>, correct to the nearest degree. Use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext><mover><mtext>A</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>D</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>77</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp;for the rest of this question.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the area bounded by the path <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>BD</mtext></math>, and fences <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AD</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mtext>Area</mtext><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>85</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>85</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>77</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)(</strong><strong>A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong> </em>for substituted area formula, <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for correct substitution. Award at most <em><strong>(M1)(A1)A0</strong></em> if an angle other than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>77</mn><mo>°</mo></math> is used.</p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mtext>Area</mtext><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>85</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>38</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>85</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>38</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)(</strong><strong>A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for substituted area formula&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>b</mi><mi>h</mi></math>, <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for correct substitution.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3520</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mtext>m</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3519</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>91</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35033819","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.2c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the area bounded by the path BD, and fences AB and AD.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}